  "texts": [
    "By substituting (3) into (4), assuming that information bits are equally probable, i.e., Pr(σ 2 0) = Pr(σ 2 1), taking the natural logarithm of both sides, and performing some algebraic simplifications, the MLD rule can be rewritten asσ2 x σ 2 0 ≶ σ 2 1 σ 2 x0 σ 2 x1 σ 2 x1 -σ 2 x0 amplitude scaling × ln σ 2 x1 σ 2 x0 logarithmic term ≜ γ, (5)where σ2x denotes the estimated sample variance of the received waveform, computed from the N collected samples within one symbol period, i.e., σ2x = 1 N N n=1 |x n | 2 = 1 N 2N n=1 y 2 n [8], and γ is the detection threshold.",
    "Accordingly, the detector decides in favor of bit 0 if σ2x < γ, and in favor of bit 1 if σ2x > γ.",
    "Based on (2) and using the fact that σ 2 x0 = δσ 2 w and σ 2 x1 = αδσ 2 w, the optimal detection threshold can be expressed as a function of |h| asγ (|h|) = σ 2 w (|h| 2 δ + 1)(|h| 2 αδ + 1) |h| 2 δ(α -1) ln |h| 2 αδ + 1 |h| 2 δ + 1.",
    "(6)The conditioned BEP under optimal bit detection at the TNC receiver can be found asP e (|h|)= Pr(σ 2 x > γ (|h|) |σ 2 0, h)+ Pr(σ 2 x < γ (|h|) |σ 2 1, h) 2,(7)where Pr(σ 2 x > γ (|h|) |σ 2 0, h) denotes the probability of deciding for bit 1 when bit 0 is transmitted, and Pr(σ 2x < γ (|h|) |σ 2 1, h) represents the probability of deciding for bit 0 when bit 1 is transmitted.",
    "A. TNC under Constant Channel FadingIn this case, due to full channel state information (CSI) during a coherence interval, h is assumed to be a known deterministic complex coefficient."
